HEADWORD: hara-kiri
<hw>ha"ra-ki`ri</hw></mhw>
<pr>(h⟦add⟧"r⟦add⟧*k⟦emac⟧`r⟦icr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jap.,
stomach cutting.]</ety> <def>A ritual form of suicide, by slashing the
abdomen, formerly practiced in Japan, and commanded by the government in
the cases of disgraced officials; disembowelment; -- also written, but
incorrectly, <asp>hari-kari</asp>.</def> <rj><au>W. E.
Griffis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

